                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5041/5a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-22T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 22, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Department has been informed by Firestone of the provisions of a bill in the
                    Liberian Legislature this week fixing a minimum wage for workmen and “protecting
                    the interest of the working classes.” It is observed that the act is to go into
                    effect on February 1, 1943.</p>
                <p>Please telegraph immediately a report on this measure and an estimation of its
                    effects.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
